            <h3 style="color:#000;">Facility Rating Trending Chart</h3>
            <p class="contentP">
                As shown below, a new interactive <strong>Facility Rating Trending Chart</strong> has been added to TUV SUD GRC Connect, which can be accessed under the 
                <strong>Site Map > Output Reports > Rating > Facility Rating Trending - Chart to Report</strong>.  This is available for both Fire and Boiler & Machinery, 
                depicting up to ten years of historical ratings.
            </p>
            <p class="contentP">
                The new web tool will appear with a default sort of <strong>Highest to Lowest TIV</strong>.  The <strong>Sort</strong> selections are by <strong>File No., Client Loc. No., City, St/Prov., Country</strong> 
                or by <strong>Total Insurable Value</strong>.  The chart shows the Active, Passive and Total Facility Score, with the applied APL factor, when applicable.
            </p>
            <p class="contentP">
                You can interactively click on any of the bullet points, representing the rating element from that year’s inspection, which will navigate you to the Facility Rating Detail page for that specific 
                rating record where you can then view all details.  The Facility Detail form has a <strong>Back</strong> button which will take you back to the page you came from.
            </p>
            <p>
                <img src="images/facilityRatingTrendingChart.png" />
            </p>
